Today is my day off. I've decided I'v done my self an injustice by living so close to one of Boston's greatest resources yet I haven't gone to the MFA yet. I just looked up how to get there and it's off the Orange line. I live on the Orange line!!!! It's like 5 stops from me! I'm a bad ex-art student :-( BUTBUTBUTBUTBUT they put up an Ansel Adams show a few weeks ago ::SQUEE:: So I'm going to throw myself in the shower, unpack my sketch book and pencil and buy myself a print. :-) Bask in his glory....

The "old guy" from work can rock out like no ones buissness.
Meat Loaf can put on a HELL of a show. He is also a nice guy when you get to talk to him, he has the same power book I do and plays fantasy games online.




Four years flys by, I love you!

so I want to start making soaps again. No idea why, maybe because I want to have a hobby, but mostly I think it might have something to do with wanting to be creative. Who me? Creative? it could happen

So last night was fun. Went out with my friend Scott and drank....... a lot.

Started at P.J. ______(something) in Teal sq. After many attempts to call people to come out and realizing I need to update my phone book, we gave up and headed over to the Joshua Tree in Davis sq. Watched some kick boxing and head out before the game got started. From here we decided it was too early to call it a night and went looking for a bar with out door seating (didn't find any) so we went to Hong Kong in Harvard sq. then to Chariles. 

And last night I found out my Uncle Bobby is in town!!!! So in a bit when the rooms not so spinning I'm going to head to the south shore to visit then back up here tonight.  YAY!

Today is going to be a good day! My sisters Chrissy and Jessy are coming in to town to go to the MOS with me. I just bought us tickets to the Butterfly Garden at 11:30. I think I will bring my camera and take some pics.

The ups of today:
Got to work on time
Had fun at "camp"
Had lunch with Rich
Had dinner with Gabe and Erika
Got out and about

The downs of today:
Crazy day at work
Unexpected mood swing in the wrong direction
Forgot my keys
I found the spider that bit me, on my shoulder
A skunk just sprayed something outside my apartment

All in all an even day

I have $15 to spend on iTunes. But everytime I go to the store I forget what I wantd to buy.
Any ideas?

I love when you don't plan stuff and you end up having a great night! 
Great night of Guinness, friends and raw fish!
Must be done again soon.

I got a bite on m arm saturday, sunday my hand swelled up for a bit and today it felt a bit numb, should I worry?

Rebecca looked at it and said it looks like a hive.... hmmm

oh well

So my sister calls me today "I found you a job!"

ok...

It's for a company her friend works for and they want to put together a broacher of their stuff. Get this I would be FULL TIME!!!! HA! So if it works out sweet, if not I handed my work out to one more person who can pass it on. YA networking!!!!


oh and I bought a shit load of new clothes :-D

note the mood, I'm not manic I swear!

Your Beauty lies in Plain Sight. Plain, simple and the girl next door. People tend overlook you as you are the
"normal girl", but you're actually very beautiful. And you have plenty about you to
set you apart, but more that lets you blend. People love the stability you have
because as others may come and go, you will always be there and you may always
be the same. You like simple things and that's what people like about you. You
most likely enjoy things most consider normal, like movies, shopping, that sort
of thing and are very friendly and probably have many friends. You are sweet and
kind and that shows on you, but you're also strong and not very naive. You're a
rather well-rounded individual. Even though some people pass you off as
just another girl, shrug it off because they don't know what they're
missing.

So my mom still rocks. I talked to her this morning about my interview tomorrow and how I was worried cause the train setup for today was so close that i might miss the train back and be late for work. To which she replied "You can just take my car tomorrow." 

Uhm, cool... thanks. 

So I go home home tonight and leave there at 8 am and be cool and stuff.... 

In other news, I still don't care for the area I'm in, but my landlords had me over for dinner last night and it was nice. I'm really happy for them to be moving to a better situation. Their son rocks! I love living in a house with a small child who is just so cool. And who I can send back to mommy when I'm done playing. :-)

Bought a bunch of new clothes for tomorrow, I even bought a dress!! Not that I'll wear it to the interview, but it was cute and Sally said I should buy it ;-) Had a lot of fun monday. Must do anime night again and again and again!!!!! Crystal rocks with her mad popcorn skills! And Erin was very nice to drop us off. Thank you sweety!

Well no work till 5, so I'l going to clean a bit and pack a bag for tonight and tomorrow.

I need instant satisfaction!

I hate waiting! Tell me now!!!!!!!!

cleaning

also they make great days to wake next to my boyfriend.

HOLY CRACK HEADS BATMAN!!!! I have my own apartment and it's sweet!!! Thanks largely to the fact my mom came over yesterday and got me and my roommate to hall-ass clean the place out. We found food in the pantry that expired in 2000! But that's to great amounts of team work and lot of bleach :-) It smells nice and looks happy. My room is kinda small, but I like it. Small spaces keep me from getting cluttered. I will post pics soon of my yellow kitchen and bright happy room. Who wants to hang out?

It's amazing when you pack up and see your life going to boxes and how few you really need. I also uploaded a bunch of pics to photobucket. I know it's geeky

I HATE my dad's side of my family! They disgust me in all respects. They have a history of stealing and lying to my Nana (whom I love dearly) The latest get-rich-of-my-mother(nana) plan was to have her sign a reverse morgage on my uncle Pauls house. That would entitle her to receive monthly checks from the government. Sounds good right? The catch is that my uncle Paul had no intention to give ANY of the money to my Nana (his MOTHER) and was never going to give over his house. Leaving my Nana in a situation where she could end up in jail!!!!
AND my Aunt Rene (shudder) is stealing my Nana's phone line cause hers got shut off for not paying the bill! Nana sold her BOYFRIEND (not her husband but a person who has no ties to the family) her house at almost a third of what it was worth. They set her up in trailer attached to the house and send their autistic son over there when ever they don't feel like watching him. AND she use to steal checks from Nana and cash them herself, that is until my sister Cay stepped in and took over my Nana's finances. I feel sick just thinking about all the crap they have put this women through. I was going to offer an olive branch and invite them to my graduation. BUT FUCK THAT! I want nothing to do with them unless it has to do with getting justice for my Nana!

You scum of the earth thing!

My mom had the great of idea of suing them for all the money they had ever stolen from her. I say DO IT!! Hell I'll do it! What makes a person hurt the women who brought them into this world? I swear that if my Dad or Papa were still alive they would line them up and bitch-smack the hell out of them.
Ok I'm not sure how I feel, but, I just had my last day of classes EVER!!! wow

So I came to school at 6 after being at work at 9:30 to meet up with a friend who said he would help me print. It now being 7:30 and me sitting here not able to do anything isn't what I had in mind. Stress levels are at an all time high and moods are swinging like a drunk Irish man in a bar fight. Blah I'll be glad when all of this is done.

Thursdays are my early day, so I got to school kind of groggy and start roaming around with my fruit cup and water (fav new breakfast) and low and behold MY artwork is hanging up around the school!!!!! YAY! Now I know what you are thinking, "you just had a show, big woop!" It is a big deal, this means that some one who doesn't know me, thinks my work is good. Hehehe, well it made me feel good. I should mention there is a lot of work up by a lot of people right now for open house. But hey I wanted to feel happy and it seems like a good reason. :-) In more related school news, I stayed home yesterday. I was behind on my portfolio (seems to be the theme) so I figured with nothing new to show and nothing printed it would be best to stay home and work on ...stuff... I got a lot done and will print tonight!!!! No really I will. maybe. My mom is planing on throwing my a party when I'm done in May or June. It will be a finish with school/ moving out party. I think it will be a good reason to get money. ;-) 35 days!!!!!!!
